Friday from 1-4 p.m. in Chilton 112K (every week with the exception of holidays).  Blackboard Bootcamp is offered from the end of January through the beginning of March several times a month. Check the CLEAR calendar at clear.unt.edu/calendar to see scheduled training events.   CLEAR provides the online Teaching Resources for Engaged Educators (TREE) program for UNT educators who want to maximize their impact on student learning, connect with other educators, and document their efforts to improve their teaching practice.  Visit clear.unt.edu/tree for more information  and to learn how to self-enroll.   The UNT Libraries offers online Faculty Teaching Resources which can be accessed at guides.library.unt.edu/gstep. These include direct links to articles and websites on a wide variety of topics including credibility, discussions, and small group work.   CLEAR and the Office of the Provost have developed the Teaching Excellence Handbook, a source for UNT policies and helpful tips for new instructors.  You can view the handbook website at http://teachinghandbook.unt.edu/.   For more information on the Teaching Excellence Seminar, contact Nancy Fire at Nancy.Fire@unt.edu or at 940-369-8744.     Contact Faculty Helpdesk: Email: clearhelp@unt.edu Phone: (940) 369-7394 In-person: Chilton Hall 112C Site Support: For questions and comments concerning website functionality, please contact: Gabe.Vega@unt.edu Physical Address: Center for Learning Enhancement, Assessment, and Redesign 410 Avenue C Chilton Hall 112 Denton, TX 76203 USA Voice: 940.565.2708 UNT System: UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on March 09, 2017 Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness 